SIMPLE: latchstring
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Latchstring
<hw>Latch"string`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A string for
raising the latch of a door by a person outside. It is fastened to the
latch and passed through a hole above it in the door.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To find the latchstring out</b></col>, <cd>to meet with
hospitality; to be welcome. (Intrusion is prevented by drawing in the
latchstring.)</cd> <mark>[Colloq. U.S.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Late</ent>⟦br⟧
